s=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rio1665702551730.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rio1665702551730.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rio1665702551730.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rio1665702551730\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Display Formats for Strings\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When defining the layout of fields with data type String, it is possible, although not usual, to apply a display format.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111824e1_d111825e1_d111826e1\">The display format codes for fields with data type String are limited because string data is normally expected to be displayed in its entirety. If more extensive formatting is required, use string manipulation and substitution functions to assemble the string, and then assign it to a field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111827e1_d111828e1_d111829e1\"><strong class=\"ph b\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">?</code>: Alphanumeric character</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111830e1_d111831e1_d111832e1\">Display a character from the input string.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples for <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(??????)</code>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__1\">\n Input Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__2\">\n Formatted Value\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__1\">\n Plato\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__2\">\n Plato\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__1\">\n Socrates\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13121e1_d13122e1_d13123e1__entry__2\">\n Socrat\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111833e1_d111834e1_d111835e1\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Any ASCII character</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111836e1_d111837e1_d111838e1\">Each ASCII character as a constant; can only be used in combination with another string display format .</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples for <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(Mr. ??????)</code>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__1\">\n Input Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__2\">\n Formatted Value\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__1\">\n Plato\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__2\">\n Mr. Plato\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__1\">\n Socrates\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13124e1_d13125e1_d13126e1__entry__2\">\n Mr. Socrat\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111839e1_d111840e1_d111841e1\"><strong class=\"ph b\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">%?</code>: Escaped question mark</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111842e1_d111843e1_d111844e1\">Display a question mark.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples for <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(Mr. ?????%?)</code>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__1\">\n Input Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__2\">\n Formatted Value\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__1\">\n Plato\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__2\">\n Mr. Plato?\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__1\">\n Socrates\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13127e1_d13128e1_d13129e1__entry__2\">\n Mr. Socra?\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111845e1_d111846e1_d111847e1\"><strong class=\"ph b\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">%%</code>: Escaped percent symbol</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rio1665702551730__p_d111848e1_d111849e1_d111850e1\">Display a question mark.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 4. </span><span class=\"title\">Examples for <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIS(???%%)</code>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__1\">\n Input Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__2\">\n Formatted Value\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__1\">\n 100\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__2\">\n 100%\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__1\">\n 80\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rio1665702551730__table_d13130e1_d13131e1_d13132e1__entry__2\">\n 80\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ljd1665702555767.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Substitution in String Values</a><p>When creating a string constant, it is often useful to substitute the result of some expression. This is done by using two percent signs percent signs (%%) followed by that expression between parentheses.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fdq1665702556618.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Extracting Values From String Data</a><p>When you are working with data stored as a string, you can extract substrings from the total string. This extraction is done by specifying the offset within the string, indicating from which position you want to extract the substring.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Display Formats for Strings Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Display Formats for Strings When defining the layout of fields with data type String, it is possible, although not usual, to apply a display format. The display format codes for fields with data type String are limited because string data is normally expected to be displayed in its entirety. If more extensive formatting is required, use string manipulation and substitution functions to assemble the string, and then assign it to a field. ? : Alphanumeric character Display a character from the input string. Table 1. Examples for DIS(??????) Input Value Formatted Value Plato Plato Socrates Socrat Any ASCII character Each ASCII character as a constant; can only be used in combination with another string display format . Table 2. Examples for DIS(Mr. ??????) Input Value Formatted Value Plato Mr. Plato Socrates Mr. Socrat %? : Escaped question mark Display a question mark. Table 3. Examples for DIS(Mr. ?????%?) Input Value Formatted Value Plato Mr. Plato? Socrates Mr. Socra? %% : Escaped percent symbol Display a question mark. Table 4. Examples for DIS(???%%) Input Value Formatted Value 100 100% 80 80 Related Links Substitution in String Values When creating a string constant, it is often useful to substitute the result of some expression. This is done by using two percent signs percent signs (%%) followed by that expression between parentheses. Extracting Values From String Data When you are working with data stored as a string, you can extract substrings from the total string. This extraction is done by specifying the offset within the string, indicating from which position you want to extract the substring. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}